Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine in both serum and blood, and marked proteinuria, suggesting impaired renal function, possibly chronic kidney disease. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, protein, glucose, ketones, bilirubin) further support renal dysfunction. Blood glucose and HbA1c are normal, making diabetes less likely as a cause. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend nephrology evaluation and further assessment of renal function and etiology.
